  description: Originally built as a civilian stunt plane for rural airshows, the
    Raven TX-1 was hastily retrofitted with scrap-metal armor and twin machine guns
    when the conflict first broke out. It completely lacks advanced targeting systems,
    energy shields, or jet propulsion, relying instead on a loud, old-school combustion
    engine. While it may not win any speed records, its purely mechanical design
    makes it incredibly reliable, dirt-cheap to repair, and highly maneuverable at
    low speeds. It is the ultimate, forgiving workhorse for a rookie pilot taking
    their first flight into hostile territory.
